	<td>
	  <font size="2" face="Verdana">
		Subject:&nbsp;<b>RE: Charm Song Help</b></font>
		
		<a href="MB_Editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=653961&TN=Charm+Song+Help&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1247374&PL=4&amp;action=REPLY"><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/btn_reply.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Reply to message"></a>
		<br>
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/Icons/icon1.gif" border="0" align="ABSCENTER" width="15" height="15">
		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 12/6/2001 12:10:59 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=15061">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Musicles" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Musicles">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Musicles" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=653961&TN=Charm+Song+Help&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1247374&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Charm works off of your Wind Instrument skill.  Since you have rarely used it up to now, you may find you are in trouble.  I suggest you park yourself in a safe spot when you want to camp and play  your horn with Invis, or EB so it will rise.  When you have a good enough Wind skill, you will find that it lights off every time.  You want to max it for your level (27 X 5 + 5 = 140).</P><P>Charisa is something as well.  You can get Opalline Earings (+5 Charisma, 2 AC) from Unrest from the Undead Bartender (or buy them).  I see them sell for 30pp each on the average, but they are a good charisma item.  There is a charisma necklace with +9 (jewelcraft skill) which is pretty cheap, and one bracelet can give you +7 cha for under 20pp.  The final item you may consider would be getting that mask of deception.  It's +14 charisma (or 13?).  It's the Dark Elf Illusion mask, no Drop, from Lower Guk.</P><P>If I am to play the chanter on a fast pulling group, then I switch to charisma gear.  Mine consists of 2 Opalline Earings, 2 Electrum Ruby rings (ruby?) - 7 Cha, 5 dex each, Sludged Girdle (5 cha), Mask of Deception (14 cha), Crown of Kobald Jesester +30 cha, Crystaline Short Sword +6 cha (off hand), Symphonic Saber +10 cha (main hand), and I have a few points from Skyshrine and Singing Steel Armor I wear.  My charisma is > 200 and my mez and charm stick.  I have found them to be successful at 120, or 150 as stated, but you will find mobs that are uber resistant, such as in Velks Lab, or Sebilis that are very hard hitting and it's nice to know they won't hit you any more when you land it the first try.</P><P>The CSS runs 8K now, if you wait, and the Symphonic Saber is usually 5K, but I've seen farmers dumping it for 1K.  The other benefit of the Symphonic Saber is it processes Symphonic Harmony.   This lowers you on the aggro list, which can be very helpful in getting aggro off you when you are hasting the group, slowing the mob, singing the mana song, and mezzing adds.  The Kobold Jester Crown is another &lt; 5K item that is really worth having in your gear.  It has 15AC, so you aren't giving up anything by wearing it, except one or two ac Points, and you gain 30 charisma.  My base is 90 so that puts me at 120 which is the minimum I will ever be for mez.</P><P>*************************************************<BR>Fast as Fast Can Be, You Can't Catch Me!!<BR><font color="#FFFF00">YOU HAVE BEEN SUMMONED</font><BR>Uh-oh</P><P><BR>Musicles Mythsinger<BR>Level 60 Bard<BR>Steel Belted Enchanter<BR>Elvis Impersonator<BR>Proud to be Human<BR>The Seventh Hammer<BR>Fires Within<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
