		<hr size="1">At level 30, Grimfeather in North Karana ran me down one day.  He agrod on me up by the gypsy camp and I lit up Selo's with my hand drum and headed for the south bridge.  Didn't make it.  I THINK I could have outrun him with Nostrolo's Tambourine but not sure.  He is about the fastest mob I know of though the spectres in Oasis are pretty quick, too.  Of course, anything with a ranged attack or root spells can be problematic.</P><P>Bards find themselves doing less crowd control when you get up to level 46 and start going on plane raids, yet sometimes a bard can save the day with a well-timed mez or charm.   Often bards are the first characters rezzed after a wipeout because the clerics need that extra mana for all the rezzing.  I can remember being in Fear -- just me and 2 clerics -- when a Fetid Fiend attacked the camp.  I hit it repeatedly with Pixie Strike until the clerics had camped, then quietly let it mash me into bard paste.  Without that timely mez, the clerics would have died making the CR pretty ugly.  Yes, 'chanters do it better, but sometimes there aren't enough 'chanters handy.</P><P>Steppy<BR>Level 52<BR>Luclin<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
