		<hr size="1">I believe the fastest mobs in the game are Shadowmen.  Currently at Level 60 with Drums of the Beast, I can outrun them.  (Don't even bring up the druid Spirit of Cheetah because I run faster backwards than they do forwards).</P><P>You will find you are a chanter again at level 53 with the song of twighlight.  This song is so powerful (even if for only 18 seconds) that a chanter cannot overwrite it. I have saved chanters so often by tossing that at a pack of 8 mobs that suddenly rush in.  You know that skinny dude or Barbie in a bathrobe is gonna die within 5 seconds (unless they have AE Mez).  So taking one or two off of them helps.  Plus the MA is whacking away on one, so now they only have 5 to deal with.  Hehe.</P><P>On days when I am a chanter in a group (Steel Belted Enchanter - as stated on my signature) my charisma is > 200.  With a shaman buff it's 240, and a chanter buff it's 250.  So yes, I can certainly mez.</P><P>Our mez has limitations, as does our charm.  You can't mez giants or dragons, but you can charm them, up to a certain level.  Also, there are mobs in Seb that can't be mezzed, called Juggernauts.  Only a chanter can.</P><P>The bottom line is get a chanter or shaman charisma buff if you are gonna play back up chanter.  Send a tell to the chanter that you are willing to step in if they need it.  I have them do a hotkey or /yell if they need me.  Most of them are happy to know you are available, at least those that enjoy living.</P><P>Now, the best thing is to be grouped with the chanter because your mana song will help restore their mana pool which burns out fast mezzing mobs.  We have found that to be a good situation from our previous raids.</P><P>Besides, they will love you more and make sure you have that good chanter haste running all the time.</P><P>*************************************************<BR>Fast as Fast Can Be, You Can't Catch Me!!<BR><font color="#FFFF00">YOU HAVE BEEN SUMMONED</font><BR>Uh-oh</P><P><BR>Musicles Mythsinger<BR>Level 60 Bard<BR>Steel Belted Enchanter<BR>Elvis Impersonator<BR>Proud to be Human<BR>The Seventh Hammer<BR>Fires Within<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
